HEADWORD: Xeronic
<hw>Xe*ron"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>xhro`s</grk> dry + citra<ets>conic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, an acid, <chform>C8H12O4</chform>,
related to fumaric acid, and obtained from citraconic acid as an oily
substance having a bittersweet taste; -- so called from its tendency to
form its anhydride.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

